Just "\nContext:\n\n\n[convert D.R.Hashed functions to take access typed Repository\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210225154559\n Ignore-this: ff515e9b3babc53141ae23fc4af2b53500f51d37b0e601f133f0d63af9f8663f5b44578880f8f82c\n \n All procedures in D.R.Hashed that access the tentative state now take a\n Repository 'RW, while 'readPatches' stays polymorphic, but reads the\n tentative or the recorded state, depending on the Repository access type\n parameter. This required to export SAccessType from D.R.InternalTypes and\n return that type from repoAccessType, so that pattern matching on the result\n forces unification of the Repository's access type.\n] \n\n[re-type the rt type parameter to AccessType=RO|RW\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210224230403\n Ignore-this: fa874ab9ec4f7f0c46fd1f26cc6f3d1ed19b3aa32c9070854f215cb844bd042b7e09f621416751d8\n \n This patch does not yet go the full way of changing all Repository access\n procedures, only some of the central pieces: revertRepositoryChanges and\n finalizeRepositoryChanges, withRepoLock, repo creation and identification.\n Commands that call withRepoLock now take the lock even when --dry-run is in\n effect. This fixes a potential race condition because in dry-run mode these\n commands still modified the tentative state on disk. Instead, the dry-run\n option is now evaluated in the finalizing procedures (which includes,\n currently, addPendingDiffToPending and addToPending).\n] \n\n[harness: remove the hashed testsuite from --full\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210225120723\n Ignore-this: bfb8e2004d4e091219fada967fe42c809027852af56d643e2c2c640908797327514f73aa8e6c60e7\n \n This test suite cannot be trun in parallel and --full just takes too long\n without that.\n] \n\n[remove rt::RepoType type parameter from PatchSet and PatchInfoAnd\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210224225716\n Ignore-this: c8490540af1d19b7995b756ab4e5879cbd2c0b374b05327d286bb1722f3c5cd370d2be0519fff3e6\n] \n\n[remove most of Darcs.Patch.RepoType\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210119150023\n Ignore-this: eee8e2332d551296501be870481b04f1d24ef7356ca9c7c91fe3a37c0d000b953b0d9064cefe2aad\n \n This removes the type distinction between repos with and without a rebase in\n progress. The 'rt :: RepoType' type parameter (and its kind RepoType) are\n kept for now, in case we ever want to re-introduce such a type distinction\n for some other purpose.\n] \n\n[remove UpdatePending parameter to withRepoLock\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122173346\n Ignore-this: c3bde2b310554f26a98d38f6cf97a0c75988b45429a4d16c53f694feb7b62e2c550f71d03a0b5280\n \n It turned out that we always call that procedure with YesUpdatePending, so\n we can as well hard-code it.\n] \n\n[move command: readPlainTree -> readUnrecordedFiltered \nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122172254\n Ignore-this: 856b5cc7a77b9b326b5907a78bbf51ea48b68bd5ffa1566246637ac0a309428138a7692efb54ac75\n] \n\n[rename diffOpts to diffOptions\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122151935\n Ignore-this: 2e1a05f0c62db20912523010477f01bb48e63cda2546126f3bb81a8856ddc785fae6cb34252051b5\n] \n\n[simplify readPatchesUsingSpecificInventory\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223204234\n Ignore-this: a73c7d343c1310e1aacb5d52c439efd3b9a97f7409a670b0e099fb532c60c74d6eececf8abdaf11b\n] \n\n[remove debugMessage for withNamedTemp\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201227203925\n Ignore-this: cc536fbeb4587d7b55bbfee3d77b63f9601c477b8e839de7990ece13b4d811b1f0f8b558a60d67aa\n] \n\n[move revert/finalize of rebase from D.R.Hashed to D.R.Rebase\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210224124453\n Ignore-this: 84d15717486d2bc4ea795d024515aa2a339476c2f0cc9943024d761e588d871bde505ad1171ed60a\n] \n\n[in D.R.Rebase replace catchIOError with catchDoesNotExistError\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210224085804\n Ignore-this: 401611f45c11df43e31fa5217dfeb5ea753ec943a7907fd09ac18600754c98711e35a66e3bbdd58f\n \n It's always good to be more specific when handling exceptions.\n] \n\n[in D.R.Rebase replace catchDoesNotExist with ifDoesNotExistError\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210120114518\n Ignore-this: deab3c80cc59e661b3bdd1e97910e1a819859cc5ac2b85aff25a154573a7d4aa03237accb6b04e08\n] \n\n[replace catchNonExistence with ifDoesNotExist\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210120113520\n Ignore-this: 30c653bf3a17b11a7a9b57a6c8eb9f976e973bf35f1d44810937488932bb1ff6684fb098666eb298\n \n Apart from the order of arguments both are identical. I like the latter's\n argument order better because it is designed for prefix use, which removes\n uncertainty about precedence between do notation and operators.\n] \n\n[fix typos in harness/test.hs\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210223143551\n Ignore-this: 418691e14854e4813682116d463f929d81d98e6f20101397a2a33d1ac53ca6aa604de798c64ae8b0\n] \n\n[replace command: auto-format help text\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122141333\n Ignore-this: 6a938a26c2611540473a7fa3a9afb3e9533220351027464c0700021d6fa95cb53a2e42019d0d7219\n] \n\n[add empty line before comments when loading patch log into editor\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210121155156\n Ignore-this: 776fa9634ea3cdea59070803852e70356c1665852e17a44ecd1b64156f1eca7abdcef0ee3fc64efc\n \n This makes it easier to reformat a changed log (e.g. on amend) using a\n paragraph filling editor command. It doesn't have an effect on the end\n result because we always strip trailing empty lines from it.\n] \n\n[fix typos in comments for command show dependencies\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118212951\n Ignore-this: c8ef92c43db47a3af32664d4743970e6bdcf7bcc6f0bc7bb1d71e075303f1d77cc7fccc36ee96ee9\n] \n\n[Darcs.Repository.Hashed: fix haddocks\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223204141\n Ignore-this: 5b2cea0c34390d97968555b686b60347d5d3909f2fc7bd2d29448b179afdcc68de19015d69595886\n] \n\n[addToPendingWithOptions -> addToPending\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122152017\n Ignore-this: 3fb0eafc7e9ce7d599e833c7dcad8d4e417c3e8ea43d0f25254182dce9b68a2d1871b95c7771d951\n \n This modifies all uses of addToPending to pass it the full set of diffing\n options as argument, which means that addToPendingWithOptions is no longer\n needed as a separate procedure.\n] \n\n[add 'darcs clean' command as an alias for 'darcs revert -l'\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210121153412\n Ignore-this: 5f8fba5651ed8833fbd2a3283fe94f2b26b5b2a6c2238e5d9ee8cc85900ba5e86d1136e59597df41\n \n This required to add the -l option in the first place which turned out to be\n a bit more difficult than expected. Adding just the option is unsound,\n because for un-added files addToPending goes wrong. However, this could be\n fixed elegantly by adding a generalized version of addToPending that allows\n to pass /all/ diffingOpts instead of only useIndex. The other problem was\n that filtering the unrecorded changes according to a set of given paths did\n not work with un-added files. This is fixed by using filterExistingPaths in\n a way similar to how we use it for e.g. darcs record.\n] \n\n[option yeslookforadds -> maybelookforadds\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122132603\n Ignore-this: 833a4bf22837ba86c696a475ff57e0baae966ebb2ecace74d9242353380aa94454b5d4325f349498\n \n This adds the default value as a parameter.\n] \n\n[bugfix: correctly unparse YesLookForAdds to [DarcsFlag]\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210122112912\n Ignore-this: eef9f6c2a2ed4876e9ea8ead85b343db950ad881b54e654020f668b72752cbc70d04467936390177\n \n This bug was introduced by patch 1d3e44c970d405378eea3081a6ca3083468d5fa3\n named \"unify diffing options\". This resulted in 'darcs status' not having\n --look-for-adds as default.\n] \n\n[revert command: auto-format help text\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210121161701\n Ignore-this: 88fe3c29a418abe163f183575bf6e85e725b08f4ae4eed52999d6d019744b01f147ad355b5bd5dbc\n] \n\n[revert command: reformat code\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210121111915\n Ignore-this: d2b7d2b9e82468abb66c7496ef147302be1f09c3a8a19b56d9c292b8abf8b646d3a113d650d3b5ba\n] \n\n[mkCache: first sort by locatily, then nub\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210110094857\n Ignore-this: c1c07c958e264c1a234e011822cf05e3be26632ecc8f6c6835082985921d11487396b780afa1c4bb\n \n This is to account for the non-standard Eq instance of CacheLoc. The whole\n point of making Cache abstract and providing a smart constructor is that we\n want the result to be independent of the order of the CacheLoc entries in\n the input list. If we first nub and then sort, then the original order\n matters: it determines whether in the result two equal (==) CacheLoc will be\n Writable or NotWritable.\n] \n\n[unionRemoteCaches -> filterRemoteCaches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210111003720\n Ignore-this: 15d89864725ae54077f8a483b27505d6a476235184c3b08fe26aaf0d128347e15e0d81724cc1d772\n \n We called unionRemoteCaches with the cache values taken from the source and\n the target repo. Both are the result of calling getCaches. Now, getCaches\n does a lot more than just reading a single sources file. If called with Just\n a remote repo location as second parameter, it merges caches from 6\n different sources: the local repo (at \".\"), the contents of its sources\n file, the remote repo, the contents of that repo's sources file, the global\n sources file, and (unless --no-cache is in effect) the global cache. This\n means that merging the local and the remote caches is redundant: the remote\n cache already contains all the cache locations of the local cache. This\n motivates removing the first argument and renaming the function.\n \n Furthermore, some of the design decisions for unionRemoteCaches were, I\n think, misguided. So I also made a semantic change here: the function no\n longer removes network entries for network accessed remote repos. This means\n that we can remove the third parameter, too. My rationale is this: a network\n accessed repo can contain locations in its sources that are essential (that\n is, if the remote repo is itself a lazy clone). Indeed the docs admitted\n that this case isn't handled well. It is true that there is no guarantee\n that remote source repos can be accessed from the local user/machine. But\n this is what 'checkCacheReachability' is for: it blacklists inaccessible\n entries for the current run and advises the user to remove these entries\n from their sources file. IME this scheme works pretty well in practice.\n] \n\n[clean up merging of local and remote sources when cloning\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210105083902\n Ignore-this: c549be1b8de465fefdc0a108760388addb604c5782abfd2b3448aac0c18be14e68026154fa54a130\n \n This concentrates the logic that determines the new cache/sources when we\n clone a repo into into the unionRemoteCaches function: if the remote repo is\n not a local path, then we add its location as a non-writable repo cache\n entry. Furthermore, the freshly created _toRepo has no sources file anyway,\n so using appendTextFile makes no sense.\n] \n\n[add a newline to the sources file when cloning\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201226174509\n Ignore-this: 876bd9ea7cbc268974769ace8b3663bcd2d0ae7289ed76ddbe291ecab8aa5e3d36184b1cb07d99e8\n] \n\n[cleanup exports in Darcs.Repository.Rebase\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210120125854\n Ignore-this: 3c83a031c1b5b002bad235f767c31650b5957fb8996ca1a8ec2fbf42ea9518f4bc9d3c25210d53dc\n] \n\n[remove all remaining instances for WrappedNamed except ReadPatch\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210119102940\n Ignore-this: 191f2085effc2e3d5b6a646f65a7bed6b7be39b38d4c4489771f33849455491c3ae142c8e666e412\n] \n\n[remove instance Commute WrappedNamed\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210119101002\n Ignore-this: 652a15854c92086d21ce68d2425d549e7f18d80c988229a3c30a954aaae6ffe2d60513c1ff9f3fc5\n \n This instance has impossible cases and we also need it only in one\n direction, namely to commute out a mixed-in rebase patch. It is thus more\n straight-forward to use removeFixupsFromSuspended directly when we extract\n such a rebase state (to upgrade an old-style rebase). This also simplifies\n upgradeOldStyleRebase because we now unwrap the Suspended immediately.\n] \n\n[convert WrappedNamed into Named directly in commuteOutOldStyleRebase\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118200559\n Ignore-this: 5d6d8201b1606d6beb504fe1427ef5af701b95dd16a23d6fe942e15179ddc3519197cbeaf54d9650\n] \n\n[impossible case in instance Commute WrappedNamed is now an error\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118200415\n Ignore-this: 6b151603883905703c786074b945d263b46c3161f50067bbd3455e9918cc47f98f9f9e0e81fce59f\n] \n\n[remove two unneeded instances for WrappedNamed\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118200320\n Ignore-this: f21bacfe9d5be9339e364e58758848de18ac84ffe7b0ca7bc984acc828f22f436ca1f001a3a8209\n] \n\n[move Darcs.Patch.Named.Wrapped to Darcs.Patch.Rebase.Legacy\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118190708\n Ignore-this: c9e334863206b2b2e83ab2cbb50191967de987a615cbd73e1b8a3b60fca4ef1663d0f6249d82326a\n] \n\n[fix the type witnesses for Suspended\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118183750\n Ignore-this: 3822b6d7422e746f9349b9f19a7764acf3b94a9df871879298c5ce7d72d05f79d1755cf431107c29\n \n It turned out that we don't really need Suspended to be a patch type, that\n is, one with two witnesses: one is enough. This gets us rid of the bad\n typing for the Suspended patch.\n] \n\n[remove an unnecessary type application\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118183456\n Ignore-this: ad9b37c1019a3e1c4615de8f954455de241f90aa7e7dcaaa03673bc5ebc3cb3643b90ebaae0e3c9f\n] \n\n[inline D.P.Rebase.toRebaseChanges into its only call site\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210118181721\n Ignore-this: 721861dcf9becf9b3a12f338da22df819d37ede16e5494c7c06def3b05c7802dc6e523c86a669bed\n \n The function was badly named anyway.\n] \n\n[t/n/issue1932-remote.sh: use fake host names under example.org domain\nGian Piero Carrubba <gpiero@rm-rf.it>**20210124101558\n Ignore-this: 4875b3020b852ecdcb42a012ba4da06fbf9e6d4dc31a4a829101273ac1b720740bf1c2fce97924f5\n] \n\n[t/n/issue1932-remote.sh: loosen the check for coping with different ssh versions\nGian Piero Carrubba <gpiero@rm-rf.it>**20210124095459\n Ignore-this: 4b20b1fec071bee91222c90b988c3fb0c8cbe901617f8cafcf3558427c2c8999d4bcb8a5b74dd567\n] \n\n[replace dependency on patched unix-compat with requiring >= 0.5.3\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210121111703\n Ignore-this: ef0e4015f4177f7863050f473e74a5d0d0036c72b07b696dafa6ad145f2f4823e91b4426e125be78\n] \n\n[resolve issue2672: extraneous \"repo:.\" entries in _darcs/prefs/sources\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201227202711\n Ignore-this: 586a7076c18ee84eb9a635cc65de1dbe51cad703de4a61a34202801aed05cc834efe6176a916c266\n \n The fix changes the second argument of getCaches from String to Maybe\n AbsoluteOrRemotePath. The implementation of getCaches makes it pretty clear\n that its second parameter is supposed to be the location of a \"remote\" repo\n (something different from \".\"). Indeed, getCaches /always/ evaluates the\n local sources file under \".\", in addition to the one under the url we pass\n it. Passing \".\" as the second parameter is responsible for creating the\n unwanted extraneous cache entries. This explains the Maybe. Using\n AbsoluteOrRemotePath instead of String serves to ensure that cache entries\n cannot be relative paths.\n \n This change makes the network/lazy-clone test fail. This is not a bug but an\n overspecification in the test. This is fixed in another patch together with\n an explanation of why exactly the test fails.\n] \n\n[remove a redundant call to nub\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201226184709\n Ignore-this: ec8d77c9b393c9e51579a98f5c7cdb5329e9ab422c6161409f3ebf26b650b43096344dbe496b294a\n] \n\n[make sure repoLocation is an absolute or remote path\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222140236\n Ignore-this: 3fbac140ee7e729a8206fefcfd7258891568be5380ee37009381550ad0d26d24c811d40fe1e23560\n \n The mkRepo constructor now takes an AbsoluteOrRemotePath instead of a\n String.\n] \n\n[remove redundant readProblem check in cloneRepository\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210105110658\n Ignore-this: 16dc3bdf0bdeeba6e16358f3d3941841c5a616b45c03c906176d31b43439e14dfc654238938c1b3f\n \n We have just called identifyRepositoryFor which check for transferProblem\n which in turn includes the readProblem check.\n] \n\n[github ci: test with and without cache (except on Windows)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210113102120\n Ignore-this: 6c4bd65b1ff4cac9aa6b63382d413071f8cb680e334e21a8428e6ceb56e83a28fb583e2b4011c751\n] \n\n[github ci: allow running only a specific set of tests\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210113101940\n Ignore-this: 6c52978a03c400e07462d98ac9e1e6185cb822c9b2319224cd91b7e3754b9ba40340e0af80237845\n] \n\n[github ci: relax versions of actions/setup-haskell and actions/cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210113091244\n Ignore-this: 681e43db77c140979577cdf41020a201a5aceef4707406d9e308c19641a6c6525ccca6ea8ef588b5\n] \n\n[fix overspecification in network/lazy-clone\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210110101831\n Ignore-this: a5c3ce8f15d4a55bc82672a4490e25231570286cced523d5372abf631f6fd8ffed03a3814b9992c5\n \n This test succeeded only because of issue2672. Indeed, the presence of the\n bogus (Cache Repo NotWritable \".\") entry means that this source will be used\n when we speculate on patches (instead of the actual remote repo), which\n effectively disables speculating. With issue2672 fixed, speculating on patch\n files now works, however it seems that we speculate on too many patches (on\n my computer /all/ patches are now downloaded). The reason for this\n unexpected behavior is that the tag in question is not clean in the source\n repo (unpacked from tests/data/tabular.tgz), which means we speculate on\n patches that we don't actually need. To get more predictable results here, I\n made all tags clean (so each tag gets its own inventory). This now results\n in downloading exactly the number of patches after the tag (42, as many as\n we have to unapply), so the number of \"unavailable\" patches is now 33=75-42\n as expected (75 being the total number of patches).\n] \n\n[Darcs.Repository.Clone.putInfo: write to stdout, not stderr\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210109184152\n Ignore-this: e9cd6541f42cc8e8b591418dc56e3d929b3038a58903a69e51eeda9a24e050204f1d4ce29adaa3f6\n \n Informational output should go to stdout, not stderr. This is the case for\n the putInfo used in the command implementations, too.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Cache: remove extraneous space in debug message\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20210109182915\n Ignore-this: 217e3a11c76aff6de8d993148aebb6b9c4c4609c90321bedc3aa89a1141a23832f6dd13766eb99dc\n] \n\n[remove catchall from show index command\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201227192554\n Ignore-this: 1feaef7822cfcdbcc2698e8c8ec3e1440df4722ec30e89f6371fca2bcb09d8f2c1c7d0b8e7ab98a0\n \n This is a debugging aid and it is better to let it fail than hide problems.\n] \n\n[add a header comment to tests/network/sshlib\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201227154026\n Ignore-this: 2db2e03a13a013281fba51dfd405a2c946144cc9f300a00257da7d56c3cb10fca94c144527c27e0e\n] \n\n[two small simplifications in writeTentativeInventory\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201226174625\n Ignore-this: 3117d0c1ed2caddfce70b25df5244b0a60f5b9f8d5d7b47f12c1dbb1b48bb71545145bea981f77b9\n] \n\n[simplify addToTentativeInventory by inlining addToSpecificInventory\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201226174338\n Ignore-this: 9c609781de838631edb31878cf342369c0d7fb246a4b4a663178f86969fe09e55eda3ffc00e6a8d9\n] \n\n[internal renames in D.R.Hashed (readRepo...->readPatches... + some more)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222135548\n Ignore-this: 32fa2747ed893c4fe0047c63d57217e2fdc3e656efc83f2937909cbb555ded8d651c1aeeed330def\n] \n\n[remove the extra repo directory parameter from readTentativePatches and others\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222132949\n Ignore-this: 4d60bfc989cd5bae171a8fb100b663363fa2ced448494e079c0a9e1248c26cf67e1b2b242273efa6\n \n Instead we now always use repoLocation for that. The other procedures are\n readRepoUsingSpecificInventory and readRepoHashed. This effectively changes\n only two internal calls in D.R.Hashed, one in finalizeTentativeChanges and\n one in removeFromTentativeInventory where we passed \".\" instead.\n] \n\n[rename readRepo->readPatches, readTentativeRepo->readTentativePatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222110817\n Ignore-this: dbd484a19cfaf52e886e6e331c9f05d12f2d024e29284848275aaafe7f38e9692f146ed262d5f438\n \n readRepoHashed is only used internally and no longer exported. This and\n other procedures internal to Darcs.Repository.Hashed will be renamed in\n another patch.\n] \n\n[globally rename readRecorded to readPristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222102407\n Ignore-this: c8ae26a66652b625914f653927ba08d016e36783aa7487a532fd06882103eb72a80851be1a56f8db\n \n Also rename readRecordedAndPending to readPristineAndPending.\n] \n\n[move cleanPristineDir to D.R.Pristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110151658\n Ignore-this: 75e868745274c628859f2fbbfb5d36d71af96cd968ab0761b5e4b36e12b2ae4bf59f2c5736819795\n \n This finally allows us to completely scrap D.R.HashedIO. Yay!\n] \n\n[dist command: simplify getting paths and contents of pristine for --zip\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110143431\n Ignore-this: 5b03bfcd2067a949d4387679c3818b825dbf5ebe8264f25b74eabce493eaacbd57f3e9f1340c632\n \n This gets us rid of yet another function exported from D.R.HashedIO, namely\n pathsAndContents. The re-implementation of that functionality using the\n existing tree functions is entirely straight-forward.\n] \n\n[simplify createPristineDirectoryTree by reading and writing trees\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110144042\n Ignore-this: cc774b6271cda4a2471d8914713418e8d9d71508b2038317f607c7bad5803935d0f743cabc374e09\n \n This gets rid of yet another function exported from D.R.HashedIO, namely\n copyHashed.\n] \n\n[make hashed pristine use the cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109143024\n Ignore-this: b6aabf4e5a092f05a0d9e7438befc266326980ed683ad6ef0b19ac074de3ebf8626e836dd7f5bbd\n \n This changes the interface exposed by Darcs.Util.Tree.Hashed. Instead of\n taking the hashed directory (FilePath) as argument, we now take a Cache\n instead and use fetchFileUsingCache and writeFileUsingCache to perform any\n IO from/to the hashed files. As a by-product, this removes hidden\n dependencies on the current working directory for access to hashed pristine\n files, since Cache locations are absolute paths (or remote URLs).\n \n This requires that we make a case distinction writeFileUsingCache, which\n should use size-prefixes hashes only for patches and inventories.\n] \n\n[specialize cleanHashdir to cleanPristineDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108132244\n Ignore-this: d1e4da31970381022749681b271a25d23d1cb6273d0803687796f2a365d5f38ec95280bc3936a15d\n \n It makes no sense to take the hashed subdirectory as argument and then only\n do semething sensible if the argument is HashedPristineDir. Indeed we always\n passed it a HashedPristineDir.\n] \n\n[some cleanup in D.R.Repair\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201106093157\n Ignore-this: a08320c4fefa60d68210763456cacfdb46745888dd853cda14ea22603b2af20e491c56b63343de2d\n \n The only non-obvious change here is that we no longer test if we are in a\n hashed repo in cleanupRepositoryReplay. But darcs check and darcs repair\n refuse to work on oldfashioned repos anyway.\n] \n\n[move gethashedFiles form Darcs.Repository.HashedIO to Darcs.Util.Tree.Hashed\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108133304\n Ignore-this: 3614b3e10c6bbaeb2b31451be165249cc16d41757b20ab7dca16185a4b58ba26f962abefd33dc1f4\n \n That it belongs there is seen by noting how many imports we save.\n] \n\n[cleanup: remove createPartialsPristineDirectoryTree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108072828\n Ignore-this: 4bd8e58b9ba2cf1a780aee69feaecf924e60df053cb1de1322fe4a5a4ccb26e6147921713b127651\n \n The only remaining call site was in the dist command where we have no need\n to create a partial tree. As a result we can also remove copyPartialHashed\n and copyPartialsHashed from HashedIO.\n] \n\n[minor cleanups in D.R.Pristine and D.Util.Cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110155508\n Ignore-this: e64c2a9d923cae0fdf0938d84bd5d881a101dea9856e2b2b8c4b9a7c4f36b516c89173f6a9d039eb\n] \n\n[readHashedPristineRoot: fail with oldRepoFailMsg instead of returning Nothing\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105155002\n Ignore-this: a2109b1f5de23ee5022d99a4df98b3c7b4b9fe7acf73cdf4638a60cce6ec658bba856dd377664985\n] \n\n[factor readRecorded into Darcs.Repository.Pristine.readPristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105153644\n Ignore-this: c909f85f6ec11c371479c595c59f330569b8ddaa2024d3d7e6328c52d36768839a6d978efa7ca658\n] \n\n[tone down excessive debug output from D.R.HashedIO.readHashFile\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110124454\n Ignore-this: a0dc2ac817cd172a16088809de99ed4d9414c48576a6dac4825c39e7db65cc8eceb8dd9d4c6d7ab5\n] \n\n[remove obsolete exports from Darcs.Util.Tree.Hashed\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109204001\n Ignore-this: 5618248bfdda2847619a27e8ea9063f08dbaed00a76fa18f1890e2f01c49c80a312766c6277a8599\n] \n\n[redefine hashed directory names via D.Util.Cache.HashedDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108124049\n Ignore-this: 400ea564f996951ccc066e70c96adefce936e85118c2925335d9f63fb72d69b3ef92e889d5f65c00\n] \n\n[cleanup: inline copyPristineDirectoryTree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105134615\n Ignore-this: 7e6ea45bf6e1aded6efc5acfed019711cec1d3d7973d0e42b15c842211c488d35aad3e35cb72272\n] \n\n[fix errors in zsh completions, add comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201225100736\n Ignore-this: 128464a1a50359ecff5ba64993d523f6eb8b0e23e8d3c3d4a1b3910272e4de5dda9b6eb68d4adc6d\n \n This fixes a stupid cut-and-paste error where I used x instead of words.\n Also, replacing the first option arg works only if the is an option arg in\n the first place, we need to properly insert --list-options.\n] \n\n[zsh completion: improve the get/clone case\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223162359\n Ignore-this: 50321e24c2b6217277682d19c7e229c1fd1417007a3edd4d0bab0d8167f2505c93c39ee418c6973\n \n Moving the special case for get/clone down into the catch-all case for the\n current word allows it to complete options and local paths.\n] \n\n[zsh completion: use '--list-options' before any other option\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223161522\n Ignore-this: b114faf220c2e8b9cf37c5f823dd8754ace003509d68d08571f68c8a4d189e8c3ac0ac19d866589e\n \n See the corresponding change in the bash completion for details.\n] \n\n[bash_completion: use '--list-options' before any other option\nGian Piero Carrubba <gpiero@rm-rf.it>**20201222114505\n Ignore-this: 3846b35e4c2bfe4e2af2fb5d9120e8686232309864ccf602dd32ad4b34d498f64c81f8beebb0fb1f\n \n This is so to avoid that, e.g.:\n \n $ darcs record -m <Tab><Tab>\n \n results in a patch named '--list-options' being recorded.\n] \n\n[fix: rollback erroneous parts of \"improve cache utilization\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201223114914\n Ignore-this: bd145a529ea8dcee2da6f771c4dc716769452c7b4a2284aec5edf3293bc3b418f5070d84f76d4318\n \n These changes don't have anything to do with what the patch claims to do\n (and otherwise indeed does). Furthermore, they can lead to unnecessary file\n download, which can make a cloning a local repo extremely slow.\n] \n\n[unrevert: make naming more consistent with D.R.Unrevert and with other commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222103143\n Ignore-this: 4cf17ec2fb0a6b5602c3be659f605df8fbf85512d5cea7c24e638adc9454707bf72f1fc1e45f1c70\n] \n\n[revert: make naming more consistent with D.R.Unrevert and with other commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201222100918\n Ignore-this: 71ba3eb57490c67b6468aef1da6228b13fe5c78c3278c24218292208e5f252b60d2b2f11dfeb32b7\n] \n\n[use promptYorn when asking whether to execute hook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221205455\n Ignore-this: 9717b654ab039fc52287c43f9f7407751731063fbe5b560b2066a47f077dab9c58dbe78cbf4afa35\n] \n\n[move Hook(s)Config from D.R.Flags to D.UI.Options.All\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221204552\n Ignore-this: 833f56f04bb68a67adb4e9e6e1af1b6ff151854deeec349f15bc9a9de9f2d557f3a8760a359d0343\n] \n\n[reduce code duplication in Darcs.UI.RunHook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221203724\n Ignore-this: 149f4e24d6fc284077e4ea8c01eefa8072f5f206e7dbb48abd1ca033cd1e519fd000988b6738b34a\n] \n\n[move remainder of D.R.Test to D.UI.RunHook\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221203510\n Ignore-this: d70bb5c6becf35737e550131ef058e7baef0d2f8ed8d588094a742b037026a441741b3b34fe06e66\n] \n\n[inline runTest into getTest and move to UI layer\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221201403\n Ignore-this: afef0d9e3558941f1422c02a697b9758709e09346d41ecd82a6ea523befb6d9ec01b9ac26194da8\n] \n\n[refactor testing of the tentative pristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105111940\n Ignore-this: f9272f165e668777a2e0c5be9d292b01f94c1c9d47897717822ba1e26be69048d27612a12c4a3e72\n] \n\n[support --leave-test-dir for all commands that support --test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105130845\n Ignore-this: a22dfbc912fc2aa2de300316729167839631018a8ff266562966687c80ad138650de94e98309d659\n] \n\n[bugfix: --leave-test-dir should be off by default\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105125044\n Ignore-this: 76d2ef56f7dc3761f38341f7a5d1accf61cac86f9df4b72f466be808afa700109622955730fd6ede\n] \n\n[record command: clean up import lists\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103171036\n Ignore-this: b40c3b56a5bc42d199c161fbdb2ca95226a8b360ae3f795714dbc1112e092b142759ed30cd93f103\n] \n\n[amend and record commands: back to using [DarcsFlag]\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103164644\n Ignore-this: a22a3637d68bba1ba1a21473b4c6ece671aedec1942f35f37937a4c586d5c02f1284930b1a93f827\n \n Introducing configuration for these commands was done as an experiment and\n my conclusion is that it has failed. Haskell's records are just not flexible\n enough to be useful here.\n] \n\n[unify diffing options\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102084906\n Ignore-this: 32c72f40a039dec4b1cefb5fe752d9e3173af9400fd36a625c6ffe5334fd25bfd5f121b9ba0fe87\n \n This lets us treat all options that influence how we determine tree\n differences into a single data type, simplifying type signatures and call\n sites. The ScanKnown repo flag is removed, instead we add a third variant to\n LookForAdds.\n] \n\n[add missing options to some optimize commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109192420\n Ignore-this: 37879f2dec790e0bb6e3df63bf2a08be2b8971109608533e2a273865753a543b6dff2e6a76af02fd\n] \n\n[rollback: simplify by inlining undoItNow\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026081046\n Ignore-this: 3f92274700e2fffdbab349c3b88818ea1674987626db0dea162de2b81fba3989e18b790d6f37b5e2\n] \n\n[cleanup import lists in Darcs.Repository.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201124082621\n Ignore-this: 18c05a87dd80c8452a6b0327a7d868f9de3c993495f7295d7f375273063c4892ff7611d3f20a449a\n] \n\n[remove Darcs.Patch.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201124082029\n Ignore-this: da69249064f4f79e7755eebae6f73e47d575fe6a9b96f41970d1760542669f8f4753404d98efa17f\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.UI.ApplyPatches\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105094020\n Ignore-this: 345dc2a2d7d3f6453037474706fb7607f8a25c72c269d91e054f5b77591c463e91e14ba132dfe144\n] \n\n[factor extraction of option components into withStdOpts\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025180815\n Ignore-this: c22992dbce3f55efeda3cb66842591a74889430f27ef5e835717e4235edef6082192e5dbf6ae802b\n \n This saves lots of boilerplate in command definitions.\n] \n\n[move stuff from Darcs.UI.Commands.Util.Tree to Darcs.Util.Tree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221135110\n Ignore-this: 839dacfab2b2bd83f9ac885625bb69e7494c0680f0d877aec920a7df7c4be78c56099739dcc236f\n] \n\n[rename Darcs.Util.Tree.isSub to isDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221133113\n Ignore-this: 1c54b42cdb737bca15ff38fe354f76b3665a8a66156ae300127dd3d5ee89d804d34c6806b01eb0bd\n] \n\n[further simplify Darcs.UI.Commands.Util.Tree\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221132431\n Ignore-this: 7c3b1c3a3638f05c1a7f4f5bbd3d9ff53dc5eee2063d971b9513854df265348d88318a993145208\n \n Use of the TreeMonad here is overkill and can be avoided by adding a simple\n monadic variant of Darcs.Util.Tree.find expands Stubs on the way. Also\n export isSub from Darcs.Util.Tree for convenience.\n] \n\n[simplify TreeMonad by removing its \"current working directory\" emulation\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221124919\n Ignore-this: 6a862703b262a0aa82637dac65b92fb1224c4f482289b3d087a73cf6e27c11b95e3772b8de68f934\n \n Darcs suffers enough from cwd issues in the IO monad. Adding to that by\n emulating a \"current working directory\" as ambient state in the TreeMonad\n was a bad idea from the start. Fortunately the only place where this\n misfeature was used is in the implementation of treeHasAnycase. The new\n implementation of that procedure is both safer and easier to understand.\n] \n\n[general cleanup of D.U.Tree.Monad\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200717174840\n Ignore-this: 6ee1b44ffb0fb971cbf9999010c4ef0dc51bf3cc834ac6a0194e4b8eb955bedf984c2e33a4f7d260\n \n This makes a small API change: initialState is no longer exported, instead\n runTreeMonad gets passed the ingredients directly. The main internal change\n is that the updateHash and update procedures have been moved from the\n TreeState to the reader part of the monad, for which there is now a new data\n type TreeEnv. Otherwise this cleans up and documents the export list and\n many of the haddocks, and moves things around a bit.\n] \n\n[cleanup D.U.Tree.Monad: remove classes TreeRO and TreeRW\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20200717173733\n Ignore-this: 54fd1d4517534debaee420a2766bd54a2db469444cbcf0cf632a96572146534fdc2384d976fba22e\n \n This merely turns the former methods into plain overloaded functions.\n] \n\n[improve cache utilization\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109144750\n Ignore-this: f38c7a912e1998a58dc4b31e31512ac7122bf1268bde6a8cac379792983d2bd893f895e65007274\n \n This adds additional (hard) links between cache locations:\n - create links not only in Directory caches, but in all Writable caches\n - add links when we write a hashed file (was marked as TODO in the sources)\n \n We have to add the --no-cache option in a few test scripts because darcs\n commands are now less likely to fail when we use the cache.\n \n The deeper reason behind this is that it will allow us to use the cache for\n all accesses to hashed pristine files.\n] \n\n[minor cleanups in Darcs.Util.Cache (type signatures, debug messages, etc)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201221100930\n Ignore-this: e539433a5b8d7c8e12d25dfaa49ce44b2ea0c6be0ab07cc15f6cbce8bbfbe4fcb4fbb381275167ca\n] \n\n[clean up import lists in Darcs.Util.Cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108091952\n Ignore-this: 3bce241918bb02606e970f6160acad8d88418a681f2933b2ee3f8d6abb19d5a78a87d57d6eef32f4\n] \n\n[move Darcs.Repository.Cache to Darcs.Util.Cache\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108090907\n Ignore-this: 2ab6a53980108adb3fd93013d86a0f73a5bae8322bb1607dce2171e5572ec4da834c36d63d91d1e8\n \n The rationale for this move is that Darcs.Util.Tree.Hashed should be able to\n make use of caches which it previously could not.\n] \n\n[rename last parameter of fetchFileUsingCachePrivate\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109130716\n Ignore-this: 817e11684bae107fcb441bbf6030525cdb622b6897947e841e961ef44ba1e8c295c554aba1886613\n] \n\n[harness: add --cache=[yn] as another column to test script matrix\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110161937\n Ignore-this: 1053dfa8b1b5f2465d3c106a1c4d51b98cb4c2c0c37ba105bb16d7ea3227dce86fed01fc6193a547\n \n This means we can now run shell tests with ALL no-cache as default. This is\n useful in order to check that we don't accidentally rely on the global cache\n for correctness.\n] \n\n[improve haddocks for class PrimSift\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105075330\n Ignore-this: 9f417b8eb485cc41a425effe403fdc72fde4b4051dbde8a1b8507e218d9fd69fb1787f4ec26efe34\n] \n\n[remove Darcs.Util.Printer.Color.debugDoc\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103063249\n Ignore-this: 90f8f7d934e2cafaf1e6f5ed26fe38a1bb35bfdc65b8e4c49f791e300204f6702aff5b87b95caa67\n \n Using color in debug messages is bad. When you redirect stderr to a file it\n will be garbled with escape sequences; similar when piping to grep and so on.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Repository.Job: use Dict to pass dictionaries\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103064250\n Ignore-this: 515973c03aa5e3956bf2361db94d0b291308a1b76e2b11130912b170b6ea715d019420ad06792ecd\n] \n\n[reformat overlong lines in D.T.Patch.Arbitrary.RepoPatchV2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103063955\n Ignore-this: f1861a853b8b2e645c0f3f3f910c7f1e61d7c323352c890d2dc7347c409945ac7438ed9cfab2a328\n] \n\n[throw out unneeded stuff from win32/System/Posix/IO.hsc\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201031105300\n Ignore-this: eedf9a6154d778876c421e9f2f885465031090e10738de71213bdb8f37d4524807ecbf7f2f03a3e3\n] \n\n[add a few debug messages to D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030080102\n Ignore-this: 36577274fabfebe1819d7c822c8f441df98bde98ce53edb817e4fcd01641d8f7a0f6a0fa506cc51b\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.R.State.filteredWorking\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027235543\n Ignore-this: 8ec8158f2d49695eac70b7d06b3c2f0b0a69ba0c119faf8502fa65d144895306003d0aac28facc42\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Tree: implement overlay in applicative style\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026190532\n Ignore-this: f35409ec96f2101b7d6f5226dca12ff3a6a64e720415bb0f4fff95090bca140db40f9dff25276717\n \n I find this code now a lot easier to understand.\n] \n\n[remove redundant call to siftForPending in finalizePending\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026100423\n Ignore-this: 5afb1366dd9eb86812e86da4efc8d3084eaba5e1c15969f6a96c87db96762db7ba252e01002f34df\n \n Sifting is done by makeNewPending anyway.\n] \n\n[D.R.State: build w/o warning with TEST_INDEX=1\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030080226\n Ignore-this: 946504ef81f636b7843b76c34ea6a89c339d1638aa27b1d83856647e36ebaf4292ce595282ea539b\n] \n\n[remove invalidateIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030085308\n Ignore-this: 3c7daf4a7c17ddedad523c00a49cf74eb7c2a2ed567045f66fc9219a67449b46a9f13a8dd716baff\n \n Instead of creating _darcs/index_invalid we now directly call updateIndex\n where necessary. This was already done in finalizeRepositoryChanges (and\n also in the add and move commands) in order to support --look-for-moves\n which requires an up-to-date index. This is now handled uniformly by adding\n a call to updateIndex inside addToPending and addPendingDiffToPending, which\n are the two functions called by commands that modify only the pending patch\n and not any recorded patches and thus do not currently call\n finalizeRepositoryChanges. The UI layer no longer needs to concern itself\n with the index at all (other than passing down the value of the useIndex\n option).\n \n For compatibility we still check if _darcs/index_invalid exists and\n re-create the index in that case.\n] \n\n[fix haddocks for D.U.Index.updateItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028075420\n Ignore-this: eeaa38ebe50545ea8d02fd5e5063920a7ee4d1205aa1a921d78675fd8c24687067c524467b065c2a\n] \n\n[index: use iPath instead of realPath\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104075251\n Ignore-this: b5ee9ed31440568c2c0b25617dbd641059835bcfe1587c85ec3a4f49ba9520f693a7a173bf6b38a6\n \n This is more consistent and perhaps a bit faster.\n] \n\n[index: add progress reports when \"reading\" (actually updating) the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104075948\n Ignore-this: 18d6b84a8f24b7273a6caafb477b8b4101beed834ebfaf4d42e3cff7afc7f727e5a8665de3ecac91\n \n Indeed reading the index involves updating items: file size, timestamp, file\n ID, and content hash are updated in case they aren't properly indexed yet.\n This can take quite some time if the index is generated for the first time\n or there are lots of changes in the working tree.\n] \n\n[index: make readDir/readFile local to readItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104074929\n Ignore-this: b0ef74b7fb41c71efa95b351da293103a5274a0eb0704ab66332c404ccd24e5c76d5513b59ad34e2\n] \n\n[use file IDs from unix-compat\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028225015\n Ignore-this: ba67f0e3f259479193eb3f716395234b4f8b3e58f7f22b04f0fed5b1d23d03ebc85e561442f38858\n \n The Windows specific functionality in the index code to get at the Win32\n equivalent to Unix inode numbers is covered by the unix-compat package since\n version 0.4.1.3. This avoids unnecessary extra calls to createFile.\n] \n\n[minor refactor in D.Util.Index.readDir\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027235316\n Ignore-this: 68ccf91cf63fae9c50e338622db9227218db699a039b519719ee684abc0f09bb523aef2efed484b9\n] \n\n[index: remove unnecessary conversions\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029094232\n Ignore-this: 344900e537aca5fcc08a8a724553e044d16baf860b3dabd77edb92a6d61800f57c555d3eb4624488\n] \n\n[index: update a few comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201104102437\n Ignore-this: c4788c64d427ce8ca890d7df8ef1785aac8f404ab15c75a5e4564ace3baa198409b85b23d3f45c27\n] \n\n[add some debug messages (index, patch index)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102171615\n Ignore-this: 38f90cd4cb8dc790bdb603004c617a858ae6c91ea531326981b59ee50cbd0cf5cd11ced927bcfc0c\n] \n\n[simplify the logic that handles existence and validity of the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029140141\n Ignore-this: 5e281f0f13f9177a1a70c84ed7f3408119eeb1f064cb90aa3bd50af0ebb8674cae5900f77cc8534f\n] \n\n[rename D.Util.Index.readIndex to openIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027233536\n Ignore-this: ce870e8084a9413c175c62c9065d33c66ebb8b43a522987108ed3cb1650020799beb32b4ab2abd31\n \n This is a more fitting name since this function merely creates a cursor for\n the index without actually reading anything interesting (besides the magic\n word). It also resolves the last name conflict in D.R.State which means we\n can now import D.Util.Index unqualified.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Index: rename updateIndex to treeFromIndex\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026173310\n Ignore-this: 19598868d0d26672147e5b17b8fadd651ad90ca7af4ccf71be501aafa3451bfccfc74b70905f50d2\n \n This function does not update the index, it merely creates a Tree out of an\n Index. This also avoids the name collision with the function from\n Darcs.Repository.State which does update the index. Also add haddocks and\n rename a local variable that denotes a tree, not an index.\n] \n\n[darcs check: add a warning when we cannot access the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030103855\n Ignore-this: 4c5b45504824df995eb90b546a1eb56e2aa34cdc2ae129b4df78a12b8e015a51582076db0a91b834\n \n This was already done for all other \"read-only\" commands.\n] \n\n[show index: show everything, not just hash, id, and path\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030095336\n Ignore-this: ffdabbdf0bf29c0ee064e78cb5ed0a4a3e13d58595669d7ffd45b4473a7516df8a8a9afb07e2d9dc\n] \n\n[index: in the docs, replace \"line\" with \"Item\", clarify size/alignment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029100739\n Ignore-this: 71d0bb4730782a801ca4a6741c47b6e4d85e67c1152b815aee9e6b11ae7f548e521ed053b47c1c0b\n] \n\n[index: use realPath instead of anchorPath \"\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029081535\n Ignore-this: 867958a2261b4b44a28fb99d7b73461cd06f0068fddf2ee4d8128be8e0f2b695baf415152babb1a4\n] \n\n[index: move update of fileid out of createItem\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029081145\n Ignore-this: 57ad500386b60dc03f58a83d877154a254ff3668813ba68d4051f2245144a65825e7fa0ef8bddfbe\n \n This is a preparation for a later refactor.\n] \n\n[index: re-use getFileStatus for getFileID' (Posix)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029075933\n Ignore-this: e977152e45278a08e184a7d1d4d2e04947c2677671c38fb6168b1337dfa7ab1d69905e43f6b34aba\n] \n\n[avoid useless CPP in D.U.Index and D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027232018\n Ignore-this: 73537921ac1721450cad27e1c8931a1d32d539baea5017e15fca1e67a218b792d1d28cb0472cdfd9\n \n We can use the same action (renameFile instead of removeFile) for both\n Windows and Posix. The point here is that the index may still be open via an\n mmapped ForeignPtr, so removing it is not portable, but renaming it should\n work on all systems.\n] \n\n[make test for remote darcs log a bit faster\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110124018\n Ignore-this: b538187e1033b81be06757382063543049d300412b41d85a4d04fadecf8dff11d5e1961ed64fd803\n] \n\n[tests/EXAMPLE.sh: explain and follow best practices\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110123702\n Ignore-this: 1835427fd5f662d2f50a23a65663a2751460e3b1afcf6b7af5a9dab7d124efc8f31364acefd24524\n] \n\n[tests/network/sshlib: use a dir local to our test dir as REMOTE_DIR\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201110110748\n Ignore-this: 983868d1c56554ad43c7d860f3005e87feb221031b6f68eccc65727364935952369d1840f677cedf\n \n This avoids filling up /tmp and improves repeatability.\n] \n\n[issue a debugMessage when catchall catches an exception\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201109170922\n Ignore-this: f526b410eee51b0562ac2f25d0f9fc3db385d7e4ce46b0a2cefe0d141c66d21ba10c4214c87e4112\n] \n\n[in optimize command, simplify path to hashed pristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201108140534\n Ignore-this: 2efbda483a7b99a580605a8f926934844755a5951d500bf9d1987c92a74d1a4dc684a03c637c79a0\n] \n\n[minor cleanup in D.R.Pristine\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105093951\n Ignore-this: d4195d74b15e6560a3063e66f0fe5ba474f97dbc79f39cab599e10a4c0f33b8f444c752274afdccf\n] \n\n[remove a useless return ()\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105085234\n Ignore-this: e9cd968e4f00e5ab0ab525be429e532e99bfa77fd982ec67533f14d6c966b20a5e8a0f11e6683b46\n] \n\n[fix the compatibility docs for Suspended\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201105083458\n Ignore-this: b1e9f20bae8d35b239b18711617170cf8ca869298fa1697a9d2e1824e7fbbdfa24025c818c93811b\n] \n\n[make notInTreeParents local to addFiles\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102172056\n Ignore-this: 2c47fb62a6de03a21df68499a17beb394625b51c1d3455701492c592a2b1c972adec9fd96c704c16\n] \n\n[trivial fix in output of add command\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102172030\n Ignore-this: 482fb479115c0b56b252fe5d96ebd78e6295310dc4bd72ae1b3e312606575a3947c1a18d37bb4df9\n] \n\n[break an overlong code line in D.R.Hashed\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102171546\n Ignore-this: ce4cb47a600b6074d6929562114f98a1fc2bfd1cd628c210c55e23003cc787fbdff9854d3a51b56a\n] \n\n[tests/issue1959-unwritable-darcsdir.sh: two more test cases\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030105438\n Ignore-this: 390f607328af396f856deb96e9c8f28c29db749b8d1cd4efdc6836a79b9b900495b6dd427fcbc1cd\n] \n\n[remove re-export of repo flags from D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030100948\n Ignore-this: 6ee94cfcdcd234ca3f857ed896261cd0a338da650f4bbd2a2ff5e10f5a446ba4dd80f6cf394dda99\n] \n\n[amend: fix comment detail\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201029140101\n Ignore-this: 756ce3e6597b587c460b6a124bda8071da969984989b30f4940b728d3f9a27d1be7ce11dfe8b6860\n] \n\n[fix comment in D.UI.Options.All\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025180946\n Ignore-this: b38a377594d5e697ac54e371da660c8df8034a320adc9e5a751a17d1170ea4d9541bd6685ce3b3e7\n] \n\n[break and overlong type signature\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025084544\n Ignore-this: a0ee00ec2290a02d137f058bdb27891c3072fc45d3802a5981529bec05c1900a0a750402b4d53a5a\n] \n\n[fix typo in a comment\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025063542\n Ignore-this: b5ab76e63e4996909a62b2cefaf2b49e779fcdee62f96356fc99534d15ec50cb2631591877962adb\n] \n\n[D.R.ApplyPatches: print warnings to stderr\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025063211\n Ignore-this: ecf9b2d66690d9a3ee2b409219cbf2dac80f57ceeea759d5696dec5787d51ec51a7068150a863123\n] \n\n[use promptYorn instead of askUser in SelectChanges\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023201737\n Ignore-this: 40c49d62e9cb97181a059226f6ef9807c948c1844bf8be93cf6d78624a774aa6b5c149e73bcca2af\n] \n\n[use CommuteFn for genCommuteWhatWeCanRL and genCommuteWhatWeCanRL\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023200417\n Ignore-this: 1af733abf5b6c2ff1338c2a308ccb3e3ca02aa5a018e29de1ce60cb4818b81ac44f76cb17e4753ce\n \n Also reformat their definition to make them more readable.\n] \n\n[add more thorough checks in tests/oldfashioned.sh\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201111061552\n Ignore-this: 19b6545335c4b1138c45afcf601a675c7551014e893b496c19090e03a6498e9857919cf83b1ccc18\n] \n\n[enable use of the index in the test suite by default\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201030141233\n Ignore-this: a34802f507e57b7222fc63ed4064510c1d7d004467d5a86aa1479018faaf4809cb0fc6546431b12a\n \n This also adapts test scripts that assumed the former default in order to\n test the right thing. We now pass --ignore-times (or its opposite)\n explicitly instead.\n] \n\n[harness: add flag to test with or without the index\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028095230\n Ignore-this: 26397cefbb94b817414fb7e02247dbca6da010d57b69b42e38cb34db23f2bd2e11527c370eacfa61\n] \n\n[index: use high resolution timestamps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201027234549\n Ignore-this: b91248ff1247519644c1f834adfe07d06cf4614aec87df91b4cbcc4313d7b8d08a1a1ca16e7696a1\n \n This requires building against a patched unix-compat, since the pull request\n is still pending. Tests scripts where sleep calls were inserted or\n --ignore-times was explicitly passed in order to work around low timestamp\n resolutions have been adapted accordingly. In the network tests I have kept\n the explicit --ignore-times when executing the remote darcs, because this\n may be a version of darcs different from the one under test.\n] \n\n[Darcs.Util.Index: fix a few minor errors in comments\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201026174645\n Ignore-this: 4f147c7e2c367028a42606c36bce535070b4e298e55e9cce0cc486a2166daabd61a50513ff043443\n] \n\n[remove extraneous setting of --ignore-times in test scripts\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025060715\n Ignore-this: 9ba7495b6266d70457f3bb50ac08abd4a2194b33adb2c9859eb02eadfaac07f45ae02d7d231977a3\n] \n\n[make --ignore-times a standard option supported by all commands\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201025063626\n Ignore-this: 33d9209da9a88f9d3f5f6a5319eea55890b5dee7e373eb79e361a7a73b8e813b8998830fa9b81a3d\n \n This also fixes all places where we still passed the UseIndex constructor\n directly without considering the option value.\n] \n\n[add tests/list-options.sh\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201102122836\n Ignore-this: 86ace49ccae317ad29524502e96a46d095f3e71f1a5fa3014f0ea22235842784fbf834659b626ffc\n] \n\n[adapt regex to ignore build directory in our boringfile\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219082646\n Ignore-this: 64be87827098db511cd8867f61e139de88a15d2907c72de75951a6ad328670fff1f705bc21e4704c\n] \n\n[default boring: replace ($|/) with /\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219223245\n Ignore-this: 90bd63dd5bae4812b6e0303b92fc80dd60049fe6b16d8146fdee9ff4815e99b657227652baee3711\n \n This pattern was used to match a directory or any of its entries\n (recursively) and can now be simplified.\n] \n\n[move removeFromUnrevertContext to D.R.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201219145136\n Ignore-this: 84b34ae587c7f0bd4e1c4852d4d6f2a148b1a84c3d0e62a7d1b6871c34440b1d43b858027834d15d\n] \n\n[simplify removeFromUnrevertContext\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201103073735\n Ignore-this: e15affba0c241f043e95d634ecec23933afbc7c12e147f12f4d091ba4a157521a607969799ad7483\n] \n\n[unrevert: use promptYorn instead of askUser\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023161430\n Ignore-this: 6fdf02c89f4d9aacb25cc013758427da87b7ca026e96e356c47666d361a1f24298d4f7eae70af3ce\n] \n\n[move call to readRepo out of writeUnrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023143426\n Ignore-this: bc2f23214bf935e0c9df7fbc8b4af4e6b8289aef3e76ff9405b9c61298163b6d11f6d22353a049bf\n \n This prepares for moving removeFromUnrevertContext from D.R.Hashed to\n D.R.Unrevert. It also makes it utterly clear that unrevert is unsafe: we\n read the repo and then modify the unrevert bundle /after/ it the changes\n have been finalized.\n] \n\n[cleanup imports in Darcs.UI.Commands.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023135933\n Ignore-this: ffbdd701ab0d0abbcbd123b7a6ce3f71b65a406e09ac40bdc41d19e8c6b4ce8faf6f416bf3b4edef\n] \n\n[move writeUnrevert and unrevertPatchBundle to Darcs.Repository.Unrevert\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023134522\n Ignore-this: 472bcd9eb2efb997410e9b52f5872efe3d41c2e7c6d4ea07cbd18ec4373e1d42b5108931d2e3b7b0\n] \n\n[writeUnrevert: remove the 'pending' argument\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023133152\n Ignore-this: e1ab863cb42b102fcd4362b4dd181ddab00c651f54cf055eaf8fc2af7d7fd0e0eebb4d068f1726d0\n \n This is a preparation for moving writeUnrevert to the Repository layer. The\n code we move from writeUnrevert into the command implementation is asking\n the user, so belongs to the UI layer.\n] \n\n[unrevert: rename some local variables\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023133320\n Ignore-this: bca26a57b29e5905e6060870b76c8e7fc7779f237c499f0e4e054b1da90cafc741dc6fc9dbdb2c\n] \n\n[make writeUnrevert take its arguments in a more natural order\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201023095051\n Ignore-this: c60f26bc98095a595caf704586a4a145ae8591d753b69142637dd0ca46803e808bd08d2a68d22a78\n] \n\n[fix tests/issue2668-*.sh: use /bin/pwd, not pwd, in exit handler\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120143\n Ignore-this: 7f5a67c117aa7f9e99082013e9a3f23c7a5fa0f4d973b745cb246ecb4f802b7865497b5864d1366b\n \n Otherwise this test fails on Windows in the github ci.\n] \n\n[prospective fix in tests/network/httplib: && and || have the same precedence in bash\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120335\n Ignore-this: 6468ed6dd03664cc57bfde458abfa3dcef38795c8e01bcb8264d3afdb87a77b4ff224283f6bb783a\n \n I haven't seen any failures caused by this which is probably because the\n first term (test -e...) never fails if the http server was successfully\n started. Still, logically the code is now more correct.\n] \n\n[tests/network/clone-http-packed-detect.sh: fix spurious failures on MacOS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218120749\n Ignore-this: 33ee55c51dce6935cfa1ed5b4fde85ac83e155c32e4bc003c9ce24520b15eb54136e921820cb7e0f\n] \n\n[stack.yaml: add alternative resolvers with work-arounds\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204062327\n Ignore-this: e1c9ab8b9a1e103dafcfa6e58f9b6c24af713a9fa77bd922a810adb786f02141d5085fcaf142067e\n] \n\n[append slashes to dirs before matching against boring regexps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201217164903\n Ignore-this: 9d56e66051c2288e69c3120a1c6af6325fa9236f17af6d8cd8150fd251c4c75bab7cdb2849f1ef2d\n \n This resolves the first (minor) part of issue2669 where adding directories\n named 'core' and 'tags' fails due to the default boring file. It also\n requires a small change in one of the test scripts, where we want to ignore\n a particular directory.\n] \n\n[refactor: use isBoring and realPath in D.R.State\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201217111933\n Ignore-this: 32544098fd575cec3d7b615bd5d3f895e78a0c5d8cfa6c35ed6b96d3dbe38714da9f77f6dffea0bc\n] \n\n[resolve issue2670: convert \".\" to absolute path when creating a repo\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218090331\n Ignore-this: b0134c1fa3d705bd3c90fa0b0c1b1ef272609d9d197127f0169d6d4e22833de5f61bb69bb7085480\n \n Note that this is what we also do in Darcs.Repository.Identify.\n] \n\n[remove the class CharLike from Darcs.Util.Path\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201218090456\n Ignore-this: 3fea8423071f42aa78ac42f611972dc84ef8e8d44c7c009008dbd05c99df412f00c1d45757d92f9\n \n We can define instances for FilePath directly, which is simpler and less\n obscure.\n] \n\n[add test for issue2668 (both parts)\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204061300\n Ignore-this: 24bc30d99efea43054f67ad14559e60b65fbbb23229dd0206b387769b6b2027fe695cab4e39ce6ed\n] \n\n[resolve issue2668: part2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204064751\n Ignore-this: 178c56824b1140350d65a1812efb558dfdfe7d28c8f1a20a78f306fea79cda54f089f909ad0aa3c7\n \n We have to catch IO errors when calling createOrUpdatePatchIndexDisk as this\n is not an essential failure and we are already past finalizing any other\n changes we made.\n] \n\n[resolve issue2668/part1\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201204061240\n Ignore-this: 29322a50f27a46b3a57e84db3d3371dd1578ccde2f02e605ee3234acbe487bfa83a39f2ca6071788\n \n This fixes the problem that causes storing the patch-index to fail if the\n parent of the repodir is read-only.\n] \n\n[tests/lib: add comments to explain special Windows settings\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201121160453\n Ignore-this: aaeb1d4c2a063135a7de5e30e2d0a50f007be6d16e756f69765fd9bf22c88b351e02b7f78eb18ae5\n] \n\n[ci: add comments and slightly extend the trigger-ci script\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201121154800\n Ignore-this: 6ce828ee632df4be16ba53d46b7b67d2bb1d4b46452e5fcfc79926e93b4f25f5e5f065492d3b698b\n \n The comment explains that what is committed into the git repo is the pending\n unrecorded state, not the recorded state. Also remove the redundant\n --pending flag for darcs show files. Instead, add -A flag to 'git add' in\n order to include pending file removals with the commit.\n] \n\n[convert darcs-2: more advice and a friendlier, shorter confirmation prompt\nSimon Michael <simon@joyful.com>**20201120221947\n Ignore-this: e69feb13e6843da1bba76efbc95082ec1bfb68311ddafb49b63c1645b3657c54d7459f3c091e81a\n] \n\n[resolve issue2667: catch IO errors in seekRepo\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201120164610\n Ignore-this: 780a0ccf1e2a6f7712849226a220de5e7aee83d100be0c60bd60a8b8f8a040591711545b278c25cb\n \n When we (recursively) cd \"..\" to determine if we are in a darcs repo, we may\n well hit an IO error, such as permission denied. We now catch such errors,\n emit a warning, and return Nothing (not in a repo).\n] \n\n[ci: reduce tests on Windows to darcs-2 format\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201120155812\n Ignore-this: 57866ee15aa04255b744af0327ab51ad6c3156690e2c40cee1b27c86f946d303739c2e0b2abca2a4\n \n Running the shell tests on Windows takes about thrice as long as for Linux\n and macOS, over one hour in total.\n] \n\n[ci: enable running the tests on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119162154\n Ignore-this: a86c78b8a1ccaec1f40154f17b72c4c1f46fa4baf8206efcec05b480a31ee8fde6692febc9d6a6a2\n] \n\n[tests/printer.sh: disable test for \\r encoding on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100616\n Ignore-this: 9834f2c3c9accab3691b69d0d95e4b38e9e7932742e82db177f3134d4e29e59acc01e6717f692b20\n \n This fails for reasons that are still unclear to me.\n] \n\n[tests: remove obsolete setting of DARCS_EDITOR\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201116090245\n Ignore-this: 8e4bca995d00a2654aec63fb91f32cf455536de429c593576278505bb810d2cae9e3137ae8283b51\n \n We nowadays have --no-edit-description in the defaults when testing.\n] \n\n[ci: restructure the caching apparatus\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119162036\n Ignore-this: b774c3273ee3ee9cd72804d26bd06bd3c9ce5efc7062ababd32458023c0afb835b44e69bbbc8021b\n] \n\n[ci: use runner.os instead of fiddling with matrix.os\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161935\n Ignore-this: 32a358dc298d6e2e9c77acee63ff2f036dd1112c9d7b0faafb5dda81464e4d6636020f76eb52efcc\n \n The runner.os gives us the OS class in a simple way.\n] \n\n[ci: add ACTIONS_ALLOW_UNSECURE_COMMANDS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161648\n Ignore-this: 2b5e1f1ca9a62dbae7dc906e306df71687b78718a8f90541e3f9f0a5d3408e42718211ff614a26e2\n \n This became necessary because of a change in the github actions. Hopefully\n actions/setup-haskell will be adapted soon so we can take this out again.\n] \n\n[ci: remove --hidesuccesses when running the tests\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161305\n Ignore-this: 9e8df4b328ae2bfca936a70cb14923f1be385c7a430ca87f57a05b4e0fb98ab6c1fb2a76daf3c2ea\n \n It turned out that when we accidentally invoke MAPI on Windows, the command\n may hang indefinitely. With --hidesuccesses it is hard to detect that\n situation since running the tests on Windows is very slow.\n] \n\n[ci: use ghc-8.8.4, not ghc-8.8.2\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119161234\n Ignore-this: f20295f38cc6eeb25740fa1ad876c8cf478b5aa5f852aa914e492f4a244f94eab2d3eb1454dc5afa\n] \n\n[tests/lib: factor out os_is_windows function\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115210637\n Ignore-this: 712b299ac3a82cbe5d72858f18fb37426159edca6820e2e8640951441c427aee8384bb79358714b9\n] \n\n[tests/lib: include \\r in IFS on Windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115222029\n Ignore-this: 968041ece52d0c702b9c776b634a6219a4701c95646d6541f108a59b0f419ddc620a7a57ae684225\n \n This makes several of the tests succeed when I run the CI.\n] \n\n[tests/add_permissions.sh: enable commented parts of the test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115110445\n Ignore-this: f76aba6923a98f75b91c03c097309a9c115ca1b359c03807f39da03939fba5a66cf2a317930472\n] \n\n[fix tests/send-external.sh so that it works on windows, too\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100118\n Ignore-this: 9e8c027b68f8b95144d590d3a3520e59fc936aa5b30135f2715c49b4a19c010853578b7b331a5b46\n \n Unfortunately it is not fully clear why invoking the generated script via\n bash does not work on Windows, whereas invoking a Haskell script via runghc\n works.\n] \n\n[more Windows test fixes\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119100445\n Ignore-this: 6a67ce0b1093f179830ea99100ee1c3122bed4283dd1ee2a72d80ce983f5c07bb130452f678ee54e\n] \n\n[add a debug message to execSendmail\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201119075357\n Ignore-this: bbeb50246430bd5e6ed26c6df23131b915e091af73e66e9003c691a29d49044887d92ed04c83510b\n] \n\n[rollback \"relax lower bound for base16-bytestring\"\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201118160140\n Ignore-this: d3862407a9e85bdddde168acc8f65b39fea36662a164452a0ed6fd3d1eead06c41ff68e395d5173b\n \n This is no longer needed when adding base16-bytestring as an extra-deps\n entry in the stack config.\n] \n\n[upgrade stack resolver to 16.22, add base16-bytestring to extra-deps\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201118154357\n Ignore-this: 45fb098bdc398ea0666f197ef911ab392a1677cabb72c9cbdba36fd139bd8e69afa02604bc7c5958\n] \n\n[clean up some of the email sending mess\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201116083542\n Ignore-this: a9c5ad49bc33a0a17a1608cc0ef0410bfd2f266f4518aa968236f990c5f53bc9a330f34348b30c25\n \n Searching for a sendmail command in paths like /sbin makes sense only on\n Unix-like systems. This code is now guarded behind #ifndef WIN32. Since we\n always use MAPI on Windows, unless a sendmail-command is specified via the\n option or the SENDMAIL environment, I have replaced HAVE_MAPI with WIN32\n enerywhere. Furthermore, the send command itself no longer has #ifdefs, as\n we pull the check for early failure into D.UI.External as (Os-independent)\n checkDefaultSendmail, adding a TODO comment that this should be improved (on\n Windows) to check whether using MAPI has a chance to succeed.\n] \n\n[remove unused function resendEmail\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201117091605\n Ignore-this: 4cbf0516e1afbae8e74ab534077741843f6097266ffa8fb444d90cafec632f9d893810fa4fb47f1e\n] \n\n[ci: re-configure git globally on windows\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115223428\n Ignore-this: 1ae5a7db209574d7bbd15b8b140fcc95c556546754d7c0854bd6b74e473fa14638a39253a9584ff9\n \n This must be done to prevent our test data from being checked out with\n additional CRs.\n] \n\n[fix broken tests/issue1101.sh\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115222352\n Ignore-this: 53ef54ffdd1843b8a04de47c615eb31123fa72ba591658a65814d9290c9b24e83fce6c63660cd9e3\n] \n\n[tests: compare paths in a more portable fashion\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115221728\n Ignore-this: 908a3961555c4f114962ec6c04d2eed5dfa354784c06554e57b81b85fa4dc3248b6b48aa316774d9\n \n This replaces the grep pattern '/filename$' with uses of test and basename,\n which has a better chance of succeeding on Windows.\n] \n\n[tests: simplify comparing patch bundles\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115041039\n Ignore-this: bebb1bb77d4f90dd93d3820aaa29ad130b8dd27eefa64f603d7cc4b4f4a3dab76e1087600bbbc294\n] \n\n[tests: more of the usual test repo removal fixes\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115210552\n Ignore-this: 97ede33c3ee76ca10c8cf057f89c6b591f8682cd30e2f93f7d1274c58bd36b2a85ac1ad24e2435c1\n] \n\n[ci: include pending files in the git commit\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201115205030\n Ignore-this: d211ae8256107cf21df0b6dce3ff6a91ee55b8af97e10b9208a3692e74ff834e6fbf7db3e0062418\n] \n\n[ci: remove hashed-store tests\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114174929\n Ignore-this: 65e59063ec31091968abd3a6ef467b43362e067a5c25ca0c80d4cb2c076ba7b90c42179c2cdef678\n \n They fail which is most probably because they aren't re-entrant.\n] \n\n[add CI support using github actions\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114170732\n Ignore-this: 31fe9e47eaaaa949452c647f9f3bc86b8f33bfc953438f3176ba8bc8f69b5a96455a2a663eb1de99\n \n For the moment this is manually triggered using ./release/trigger-ci. This\n script takes the basename of the current directory as the git branch name,\n makes sure we are inside a darcs repo, and then creates an automatic commit\n on that branch (creating it if necessary), then force-pushes that branch to\n the github repo, which will trigger the CI run. If a .git does not exist\n yet, it will be created, which means your branch will be reset to this\n snapshot as the first and only version. The configuration of the job to run\n is in .github/workflows/build-and-test.yml. Windows tests are currently\n disable because they run into errors I have no idea how to fix.\n] \n\n[simplify usage of darcs-test\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201028091831\n Ignore-this: 7c84560f34a06407c8fc3b5744ddabc981d6000839999d14ef8441fe0d9648b29ff01eb90219758\n \n The UI to select which darcs formats to test, which test suites to run, and\n which diff algorithms to use is changed so that the user now directly\n specifies these sets as strings, rather than having to supply a separate\n flag for each variant. This is much more convenient to use.\n] \n\n[remove the \"compiled on <timestamp>\" from exact version\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114065931\n Ignore-this: e1054c592f1627673b4196c813c5c3d18c39800aa80832d9005a6a8219bfe5fdbd1a995d885b215d\n \n This information is not of much help and makes it impossible to create darcs\n binaries reproducably. It also causes problems when building in MacOS.\n] \n\n[tests: some portability fixes for MacOS\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201114104632\n Ignore-this: d2c5de6b3dd4ee2a5c19db6bdf197281bbeff5871f5b3c44e4646392c2c7cbf36b5d2f74c6ca71f4\n \n Defaulting the directory argument of find to \".\" is is a GNUism and doesn't\n work on MacOS. Similarly, 'wc -l' on MacOS has spaces in its output, the new\n code is simpler and more portable. Also the test command in the MacOS bash\n apparently cannot handle the '!' operator.\n] \n\n[Fix gen-version-info.hs to work in snapshots\nGanesh Sittampalam <ganesh@earth.li>**20201111211803\n Ignore-this: 871ef56dd89222eb69919263e4c15c71d07a9659753a47359c1739157c1be23dbb3e7587736743cb\n \n Commands such as \"darcs test\" just copy the tree without\n _darcs, so we need the build to work in those situations\n without having pre-generated files available.\n] \n\n[TAG 2.16.3\nBen Franksen <ben.franksen@online.de>**20201022094642\n Ignore-this: bd76d7e31488721e4a5ce7267115e71c3b68d680c155c75c3dd275d9e54933a607d208fab502a143\n] \n"